Algflowering: The levels decline in Pinellas, Manatee and Sarasota
The latest report from the Florida Fisheries and Wildlife Commission shows a general decrease in the concentrations of algal flowering for parts of the area around Tampa Bay.
According to the Commission, uneven flowers are reported in the areas around the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier, which may indicate decreased levels.
The algflower stretches along about 20 miles [20 km] of the coast, from northern Pinellas to southern Lee.
Spots can be seen about a mile into the sea outside the big municipality of Hillsborough, but in fewer places than last week.
Algblooming has also been observed in the large municipality of Pasco.
Middle-high concentrations on or off the coast of Pinellas have been reported during the past week. Outside the Hillsborough coast low to high concentrations, background concentrations to high concentrations in Manatee, background concentrations to high concentrations on or off the coast of Sarasota, background concentrations to medium-high concentrations on or off the coast of Lee, and low concentrations in Collier.
Reports on respiratory irritation continue to come from the major municipalities of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
There were no reports of respiratory irritation in northwest Florida during the past week.
